$interpreted:
Fatima: Ever since Rune Academy came to the Valley,
our lives have become tougher and tougher!
Panther Hunter: Yeah! We can barely catch any prey now!
Panther Resident: So many plants are no longer growing too!
Fatima: Since their arrival, haven't they disrupted our lives? Haven't they challenged the cultures and customs we take so much pride in!?
Panther Hunter: Last time, they even trespassed into the hunting grounds and scared away my prey.
Panther Resident: My old home that no one lives in right now is filled with their trash. They even plucked out all the nearby flowers!
Fatima: Right now, they are even trying to use Rune magic to annihilate the Panthers and take control of the entire Whistlewood Valley.
Fatima: As a brave member of the Panthers, what should we do!?
Panther Resident: Protect our homeland!
Panther Hunter: No more tolerance! Chase them away!
Fatima: Warriors who want to show the Rune Academy the pride of us Panthers, come with me! Today, we are letting them feel our wrath and pay the price!
Fatima: Let's go!
Panther Warrior: Captain Fatima, the warriors are all ready to go.
Fatima: Very well. Return to the group first. I'll go scout out the path further ahead to ensure our safety.
Panther Warrior: Understood. Please be careful.
Fatima: ...Great, nobody's stationed here in this area around the Academy.
Fatima: When the sun rises, we'll take care of the guards at the entrance. Then we'll be able to charge inside and catch those bastards by surprise.
Fatima: Charle, why are you here!?
Charle: I know what you people are planning to do.
Charle: Please stop. I do not want this to become a bloody war between the two sides.
Fatima: Stop pretending. You people are the ones who forced us to choose this path!
Charle: No, this is a misunderstanding. Please let me explain...
Fatima: No more talking! I'll take care of you first!
Fatima: ...I won?
Fatima: Thank goodness. Now, nobody can stop us from attacking Rune Acade...
Fatima: What!?
Fatima: What are you doing!
Panther Warrior: Kill her!
Fatima: ...Damnit!
